Making the best of a bad situation (thanks for nothing, Covid), Chez Oskar has set up a plethora of nicely distanced seating both on the sidewalk, and under tents on the street. The staff is incredibly nice and accommodating, and the food is exactly what it should be. Tasty, filling and well-prepared, and in some cases, excellent. The fish part of the fish and chips was light and flaky and not even a little greasy, and the Peruvian chicken was well-seasoned with a cracking crisp skin. I enjoyed my blackberry sidecar so much I had two, which doesn't happen often. This isn't haute cuisine, but it was very satisfying and the staff brought everything up to five stars.

If I could give this place 10 stars on the food alone I would. Holy smokes talk about the most delicious fresh ingredients and flavors. I'm a huge foodie and super critical about meals when I eat out. This is the best meal I have had the entire year of 2020. I'm officially addicted to this place! It's nice to be able to eat outdoors with my pup safely and socially distanced. It's a cute little place and set-up very nice ambiance and servers. It was my first time eating here with my friend and my fur baby. Now let's get to the food we had the grilled squid chili charred as an appetizer. Not only was it a good sized portion that would've been satisfying as a meal for one person. The flavors OMG!! The squid was cooked to perfection with the perfect hint of a chili that left a nice little kick but very subtle so perfect for those who have trouble with anything spicy this won't bother you at all. The zucchini and lemon that wer grilled with it in this incredible sauce with scallions were so tender. For our main entrees I had the most delicious Spicy Salmon burgers cooked and seasoned to perfection with a small salad and steak fries, chipotle mayo. It was so satisfying and tasty my friend had the Shrimp and Calamari Pineapple risotto that looked like heaven a good sized portion for your money and she it tasted amazing the addition of the pineapple gave it a sweet refreshing taste to balance out the heat of the risotto and the Calamari and shrimp were phenomenal cooked to perfection! The drinks we also we're out of this world the socialite was my personal favorite that is a Gin base with refreshing cucumber. Really high quality Gin with a sweetness did not leave me with a dry throat after like most cheaper gins do. What else can I say this place is officially my favorite new place in the neighborhood. They also offer Brunch/Breakfast style dishes all day for those who love to eat breakfast anytime of day. If you're in Bedstuy or visiting the neighborhood it's a must eat destination

Unfortunately, I was only able to experience the takeout option of this establishment but that did not appear to complicate the care taken to prepare  the food or the delightful attitude of the takeout window staff. I was in a party of three: 2 orders of the spicy salmon burger and 1 of the veggie burger. I opted to upgrade to sweet potato fries. My only complaint might be that the sweet potato fries were more like long chunks of baked sweet potato and did not possess any crispy fried texture. Fear not though, the traditional fries are exactly what you would expect. The salmon patty itself was incredibly flavorful and the side salad that accompanied it went well on top of it to add more flavor and texture. The spicy aioli that came on the side was also damn good. Pro tip: Ask for extra to dip your fries in. The quinoa based veggie patty did not lack flavor like it lacked the ability to stay in patty form. However, once the bun was abandoned (truly unfortunate as the buns were great), the side salad embraced the disparate pieces with open arms. All in all, a great dining experience.

When I entered the restaurant, I was greeted by a wonderful, inviting atmosphere with a colorful painted ceiling on one side and a group of hanging polka dotted umbrellas on the other side. When we sat down we decided to order the lamb burger and the croque merguez. The croque merguez came with two perfect sunny side up eggs, as well as crispy cheese for texture. The sausage gave it an extra kick of flavor. The side salad was also a great palate cleanser between bites. The lamb burger was tender and flavorful although simple. I decided to get a fried egg to spice it up a bit (definitely recommend) if you decide to get this burger I would recommend layering it with some of their additional toppings to complement the burger and the goat cheese. I also decided to swap out regular fries for truffle fries, I am happy to say that the truffle wasn’t too overpowering and was the perfect side dish. All in all, its a very reasonably priced brunch spot in the neighborhood, and I definitely would go back for dinner.

In France this place would be comparable to a very good what we call “Brasserie”. They’re pretty difficult to find, even in France. Profit is driving a lot of professionals to go cheap on ingredients which is despicable. This place is not one of those nasty places. Last but not least, the staff is the bomb. This place never disappoints.

We ordered 3 appies and 1 dessert. The pear and blue cheese salad was delicious. The blue cheese was not stinky, but rather had a smoky taste. The duck taco, needed more seasoning. The lime on the side did not help it. The lobster crepe was silky. But the best dish of the night, was the chocolate dessert. Warm, moist, slightly sweetened, and paired with ice cream, it was the perfect end to the evening. Definitely would be interested in their entrees next time.

Truly excellent experience at this restaurant. Everything was cooked to perfection. Wine list and bar both very well stocked with just the right amount of quality options across a range of price points. Service was very attentive and friendly (and in at least one case authentically native-speaking French!). Staff was welcoming and hospitable, and the gentleman that was assisting me for the latter half of my meal made wonderful suggestions. Decor is quaint and cozy, and belies the underlying quality of the service and food: the unassuming appearance underpromises and the incredible quality and value of the food and drinks along with the great service overdeliver.  Absolutely check this place out! Just don’t take my table!

I went here on a date. Not to be confused with dating, I ain't dating anyone. hahaha. (Cultural gap thing need an explanation). Okay enough about me.  Chez Oskar is definitely a bring a date here type of vibe, so swexi.  Let's start with the wonderful bar-staff. Devin and the lady whose father was in the military (I forgot her name) were delightful. Imagine, even after they were closed and I'm sure very tired, they didn't once move to kick us out.  The space on first glance can look congested but isn't at all. There's enough room at tables for long legs and big arms, not my date's. We sat at the bar, isn't that the place to be? There are two sides, one with the bar and a few dinning tables and on the other side same bar and seating set up but larger.  We tried a hibiscus something drink which includes egg whites, the date loved it. That along with house wines and of course water de water satisfied our thirsty selves.  The salad, olives and octopus and bread were very filling starters and went down divine. We decided against entrees as we were filled. My only complaint was the octy could have been a tad softer, it was a bit too chewy. No, I've had softer so yes it can be done that way. When we decided to try something else the kitchen was closed but we were informed when they were gonna so our fault we waited that long.  The decor is very artsy which your girl adored and of course my damn camera phone had to be messy that evening not allowing me to take fitting pics. Damn you Android!  I will be back, especially as I now live next door.  The End.

On the corner of Decatur and Malcolm X, this quaint restaurant is absolutely astounding to stumble into. My partner and I ordered the spicy lamb burger- which was delectable. With a side of mixed greens and fries, topped with goat cheese, this dish is one I highly recommend. Additionally, we ordered sangria that was reminiscent of Europe. Our server was kind, personable and patient. The space is longer than it is wide, with a polarized aesthetic. On one side, there is a full bar with a line of tables and windows that open the corner to a view of the intersection. Adjacent to such is another room that opens tall and wide with a wall of windows, eclectic artwork and interesting shades of various colors. All with a French cuisine and historical idiosyncrasies- this place is beautiful.
